# Shoe Health Terms of Service

**Effective Date:** 08.11.2024

## 1. Acceptance of Terms

Welcome to **Shoe Health**! By downloading, accessing, or using the Shoe Health app (the “App”), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service (“Terms”). If you do not agree to these Terms, please do not use the App.

## 2. Description of Service

Shoe Health is a mobile application that helps users monitor the lifespan of their running shoes by tracking workouts, wear patterns, and performance data from Apple Health. Shoe Health enables users to make informed decisions about shoe replacement and helps optimize workout performance and safety. The App is intended for personal use only.

## 3. Eligibility

To use Shoe Health, you must be at least 14 years old. By accessing or using the App, you represent and warrant that you meet this eligibility requirement.

## 4. License and Use of the App

Shoe Health grants you a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to use the App in accordance with these Terms. You agree not to:
- Copy, modify, distribute, or create derivative works based on the App;
- Attempt to reverse engineer or extract source code from the App;
- Use the App for commercial purposes without prior written permission from **[Your Company]**.

## 5. Subscriptions and Payment

Shoe Health offers both a free version and a premium subscription option:
- **Free Version**: Users can track up to five pairs of shoes.
- **Premium Subscription**: Unlocks unlimited shoe tracking, advanced insights about show wewar, performance and statistics..

By purchasing a premium subscription, you agree to pay the specified fees. Subscriptions renew automatically unless you cancel at least 24 hours before the current period ends. You can manage your subscription settings in your Apple ID Account.

## 6. Data from Apple Health

Shoe Health requests access to specific Apple Health data, including running workouts, heart rate, step count and other performance metrics, to provide accurate tracking and insights. By granting access to Apple Health data, you agree that Shoe Health may use this data solely for in-app calculations to assess shoe wear. The App does not store this data permanently or share it with third parties.

## 7. Data Storage and Security

- **Shoe Profiles**: Your custom shoe profiles are securely stored on your device and in **iCloud**, enabling access across your Apple devices.
- **Apple Health Data**: All data imported from Apple Health (workouts, distance, heart rate, step count, and running power) is used only for temporary in-app calculations and is not stored anywhere on our servers or in the app.
- **No Third-Party Access**: Only you have access to this data, with no external sharing.

## 8. User Conduct

As a user of Shoe Health, you agree to:
- Use the App only for its intended purpose;
- Refrain from engaging in any activity that interferes with or disrupts the App;
- Comply with all applicable laws and regulations while using the App;
- Refrain from using the App in a way that may harm Shoe Health, other users, or third parties.

## 9. Changes to the Terms of Service

We reserves the right to modify these Terms at any time. Any changes will be posted within the App and become effective upon posting. Continued use of the App following any changes to the Terms constitutes acceptance of those changes. We encourage you to review the Terms periodically to stay informed.

